  "title": "Feature: RangeInput",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nFix #2317 \r\n\r\n* Finally choose to implement `RangeInput` with the connector `connectRangeSlider` instead of `connectPriceRanges` because the logic was really the same. Maybe try in upcoming versions to manage `PriceRanges` with `connectRange` both share similarities (boundaries, range).\r\n\r\n* The markup is the same as RIS\r\n\r\n* Deprecation for the connector `connectRangeSlider` for `connectRange`\r\n\r\n* Jest enzyme serializer added to be able to handle Snapshots with Enzyme\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nYou can play with the `RangeInput` on dev-novel.",
